GOPI KALLAYIL: Good afternoon.

00:00:05.199 --> 00:00:06.240
My name is Gopi Kallayil.

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:08.730
And I'm delighted to
welcome to the Google

00:00:08.730 --> 00:00:12.600
campus for the fourth
time Radhanath Swami,

00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:20.020
the author of the international
bestseller "The Journey Home"

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:22.310
and now the "New York
Times" bestseller,

00:00:22.310 --> 00:00:24.718
"The Journey Within."

00:00:24.718 --> 00:00:28.120
I had my first
opportunity to learn

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:33.405
about Radhanath Swami of all the
things in a video about Burning

00:00:33.405 --> 00:00:33.905
Man.

00:00:37.190 --> 00:00:39.570
He does get around to the
most interesting of places.

00:00:39.570 --> 00:00:42.140
But during the
Burning Man interview

00:00:42.140 --> 00:00:44.140
in response to a
question, he said,

00:00:44.140 --> 00:00:46.250
everybody's looking
for happiness.

00:00:46.250 --> 00:00:50.320
And in search of the happiness,
we change your externalities.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:51.800
Whereas, to find
true happiness, we

00:00:51.800 --> 00:00:53.265
need to shift our consciousness.

00:00:56.490 --> 00:00:58.140
And the way Radhanath
Swami reached

00:00:58.140 --> 00:01:00.630
this very important
insight was through

00:01:00.630 --> 00:01:03.730
his own personal journey,
where when he was 19 years old,

00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:05.710
he left Chicago.

00:01:05.710 --> 00:01:08.320
And in search of what is the
source of true happiness,

00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:11.740
he hitchhiked his way across
Europe, Central Asia, all

00:01:11.740 --> 00:01:14.980
the way to India
and arrived there

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:17.330
on the borders with no money.

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:19.500
And they would not let him in.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:24.010
And he persuaded them
to allow him to come in.

00:01:24.010 --> 00:01:27.850
And he said you would do
something for humanity

00:01:27.850 --> 00:01:30.129
at large and, particularly,
for the people of India.

00:01:30.129 --> 00:01:31.670
But during the course
of his journey,

00:01:31.670 --> 00:01:35.560
what he realized that the
cost for most problems in life

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:39.040
was human frailties that happen
irrespective of who you are

00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:40.840
and what your background is.

00:01:40.840 --> 00:01:43.850
And he's committed
himself to really studying

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:46.960
human consciousness, the
relationship between people,

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:50.580
and how that can be
a source of happiness

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:52.900
if you approach
it the right way.

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:57.570
And in exploring
all of these issues

00:01:57.570 --> 00:01:59.530
with very little
resources-- as a monk,

00:01:59.530 --> 00:02:01.220
he has no bank
account, no money.

00:02:01.220 --> 00:02:03.510
But he's managed to persuade
a large group of people

00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:08.020
to work alongside him and create
several humanitarian projects

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:11.410
around the world, including
a midday meal program that

00:02:11.410 --> 00:02:15.010
feeds 1.2 million children
every school day in India,

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:18.500
ecovillage outside Mumbai,
a hospital that provides

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:22.110
free or low cost holistic care,
and a number of other projects

00:02:22.110 --> 00:02:25.930
like that around the world,
demonstrating to us that, more

00:02:25.930 --> 00:02:29.360
than resources, it is like an
inner commitment that comes

00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:32.860
from somewhere deep within,
as the path of yoga dicted,

00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:37.700
that can really allow us to
manifest our fullest potential.

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:40.980
And here to discuss
more about this topic

00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:44.150
and to explore this with
us-- his own journey,

00:02:44.150 --> 00:02:46.532
as well as what it
means in our lives--

00:02:46.532 --> 00:02:47.990
please help me
welcome to the stage

00:02:47.990 --> 00:02:51.540
at Google for the fourth
time Mr. Radhanath Swami.

